<task id="087" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r6">
  <metadata>
    <title>D-D-08 Vertical-Slice Integration Test тАФ Summarize Playbook End-to-End Exercises Every Pillar</title>
    <phase>Phase D тАФ Command Router + Integration + Closeout</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>10 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>029, 049, 079, 084, 085, 086</dependencies>
    <blocks>088</blocks>
    <tags>integration-test, e2e-test, bff-api, frontend, ai</tags>
    <rigor-hint>STANDARD</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>End-to-end validation per spec ┬з6 Vertical-Slice Validation Target тАФ exercises every pillar. STANDARD rigor (validation-only; no new architectural code) but high-stakes due to coverage breadth. Test failures here surface cross-pillar contract drift that must be fixed before wrap-up.</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>D-G2</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>This single test exercises BOTH BFF + frontend in an integrated chain; runs serially after all Phase A/B/C/D component tasks complete; cannot be parallelized.</parallel-reason>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Build the vertical-slice integration test per spec ┬з6 "Vertical-Slice Validation Target" +
    design.md ┬з6. This is the binding end-to-end verification that R6 architecture convergence
    actually delivered: executing a Summarize playbook via `/summarize #file.docx` exercises
    EVERY pillar end-to-end.

    The test SHALL cover, as ONE coherent scenario, all of:

    **Pillar 1 (persona data-driven)** тАФ Persona resolved from `sprk_aipersona` Dataverse entity
    via `IScopeResolverService.ResolveAsync()`. Verifiable via test assertion that
    `SprkChatAgentFactory.CreateAgentAsync` does NOT call legacy `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()`.

    **Pillar 2 (data-driven tool registry)** тАФ Tool list assembled from `sprk_analysistool` rows
    with `AvailableInContexts тИЛ "Chat"`; chat agent receives the data-driven list via
    `ToolHandlerToAIFunctionAdapter`. Verifiable via test that no hardcoded tool-class
    instantiation occurs in `ResolveTools()`.

    **Pillar 3 (generic invoke_playbook)** тАФ `/summarize` triggers `invoke_playbook("summarize-document-for-chat@v1", ...)`
    via `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade. Verifiable via test that `InvokeSummarizePlaybookTool` C#
    file no longer exists + LLM sees single generic tool.

    **Pillar 4 (PlaybookExecutionEngine routing with FK chain)** тАФ `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator`
    routes via `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync(playbookId)`; FK chain
    (playbook тЖТ node тЖТ action) traverses to `SUM-CHAT@v1`. Verifiable via test that no
    `GetByCodeAsync("SUM-CHAT@v1")` alternate-key lookup remains in chat path.

    **Pillar 5 (output schema + schema-aware rendering + CapabilityRouter dedup)** тАФ
    `sprk_analysisaction.outputSchema` is populated for SUM-CHAT; node config has
    `destination: "chat"`; widget renders array (`tldr` as bullets) + object (`entities` as
    labeled key-value blocks); ONE user intent тЖТ ONE render (no duplicate fire). Verifiable via
    snapshot test on rendered output.

    **Pillar 6 (workspace state in prompt + tab updates + execution trace)** тАФ Workspace state
    snapshot included in agent system prompt at turn time (Pillar 6a); user can click
    "Send to Workspace" + "Make it shorter" + `/clear` work (Pillar 6b); Context pane shows
    live execution trace via additive `context.*` events (Pillar 6c). Verifiable via
    PaneEventBus event capture + telemetry assertions.

    **Pillar 7 (memory composition)** тАФ Recent verbatim + compressed mid + pinned + retrieved
    old all present in prompt assembly (`MatterMemoryService` wired). Verifiable via
    system-prompt snapshot showing memory block.

    **Pillar 8 (command router)** тАФ `/summarize #file.docx` parses to `Intent {command:'summarize',
    references:[{type:'file',...}]}`; SoftSlashRouter decorates payload; ReferenceResolver
    resolves; CapabilityRouter Layer 1 pre-selects SUM-CHAT route.

    **Pillar 9 (widget visibility contract)** тАФ Per-turn agent prompt builder gathers
    `getAgentVisibleState()` from each Assistant-visible tab; respects `visibleToAssistant: true`
    filter. Verifiable via prompt snapshot showing only visible widget state.

    **Conversational refinement** тАФ After playbook output, user types "make it shorter"; agent
    responds conversationally with NO tool call (NFR-01 preserved).

    BFF-touching task: VERIFY publish-size baseline per NFR-02 (тЙд+5 MB total across R6;
    cumulative tracking from prior tasks). Report delta vs prior baseline in task notes.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior integration-test engineer with deep familiarity with the Spaarke AI platform across
    BFF + frontend + Dataverse. Comfortable with end-to-end test design that exercises 9
    architectural pillars in a single coherent scenario.
  </role>

  <goal>
    Vertical-slice integration test exists at `tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/`
    (BFF) + a paired frontend e2e test at `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/tests/e2e/`. Test exercises
    every pillar in one coherent Summarize scenario. All 11 pillar acceptance checks green.
    Conversational refinement after playbook output verified. BFF publish-size delta recorded.
  </goal>

