  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 1**: Persona resolved from `sprk_aipersona` Dataverse entity; no hardcoded `BuildDefaultSystemPrompt()` call (assertion in BFF test).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 2**: Tools assembled from `sprk_analysistool` rows; no hardcoded tool-class instantiation (assertion).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 3**: `/summarize` triggers `invoke_playbook` via `IInvokePlaybookAi` facade; specialized bridges removed.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 4**: `SessionSummarizeOrchestrator` routes via `PlaybookExecutionEngine.ExecuteAsync(playbookId)`; FK chain traversed; no alternate-key lookup.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 5**: Output renders schema-aware тАФ tldr as bullets, entities as labeled key-value blocks; ONE render per user intent (no duplicate-fire).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 6a**: Workspace state snapshot included in agent system prompt at turn time (prompt snapshot assertion).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 6b**: "Send to Workspace" + "Make it shorter" + `/clear` all work end-to-end.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 6c**: Context pane shows live execution trace; additive `context.*` events emitted; ADR-015 hygiene verified (no user message text in events).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 7**: Memory composition includes recent verbatim + compressed mid + pinned + retrieved old; verifiable via prompt snapshot.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 8**: `/summarize #file.docx` parses + decorates + resolves + routes via CapabilityRouter Layer 1 strong-intent path.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Pillar 9**: Per-turn prompt builder respects `visibleToAssistant: true` filter; widgets opt-in via `getAgentVisibleState()`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">**Conversational refinement (NFR-01)**: After playbook output, "make it shorter" gets conversational response with NO tool call.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta vs Phase C exit baseline reported; cumulative R6 delta тЙд+5 MB (NFR-02); hard ceiling 60 MB respected (ADR-029).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All 11 pillar acceptance checks green; vertical-slice scenario passes end-to-end.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <ui-tests>
    <test name="Vertical-Slice End-to-End">
      <url>https://{org}.crm.dynamics.com/main.aspx?appid={app-id}&amp;pagetype=control&amp;controlName=spaarke_SpaarkeAi</url>
      <steps>
        <step>Upload a test document (engagement-letter.docx) as session file</step>
        <step>Open conversation pane in matter context</step>
        <step>Type `/summarize #engagement-letter.docx` and submit</step>
        <step>Verify workspace tab appears with bulleted tldr + labeled entities</step>
        <step>Verify Context pane shows execution trace timeline</step>
        <step>Click "Send to Workspace" on chat assistant message; verify tab created</step>
        <step>Type "make it shorter" as refinement; verify conversational response (no tool call)</step>
        <step>Type `/clear`; verify session resets without LLM call</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>End-to-end scenario completes; all visible affordances functional</expected>
    </test>
    <test name="Dark Mode Compliance (ADR-021)">
      <steps>
        <step>Toggle dark mode</step>
        <step>Run the vertical-slice scenario</step>
        <step>Verify all surfaces (workspace widget, context trace, help drawer) adapt</step>
      </steps>
      <expected>All R6 UI surfaces use Fluent v9 semantic tokens per ADR-021</expected>
    </test>
  </ui-tests>
</task>
